What is active listening? Active listening is the process of listening to another person fully and completely while they are speaking. It involves paying close attention to the speaker and to the information they are sharing. It is also necessary to take notes, ask questions and paraphrase what the speaker is saying. The goal of active listening is to learn as much as possible about the speaker, their situation and their needs.
